Promptly - Interactive AI Prompting Platform
Brief Overview:
- An interactive web app that guides users through an iterative decision-tree of clarifying questions to craft and refine AI prompts for any large language model.

Key Goals:
- Iterative prompt enhancement via AI-generated questions
- Two UI modes: simple editor with live suggestions and a D3.js decision-tree visualizer
- User profiles, session sharing, and version history
- Selection of external target models (e.g., GPT-4, Claude, Llama) with internal refinement on Google Gemini 2.5

Core Features:
- Session Management: Create/update sessions; store nodes and layouts in MongoDB
- Q&A Loop: Single-question iterations with predefined or custom answers; loop until final prompt
- Simple Editor: Side-by-side draft and history, inline autocomplete (Monaco/CodeMirror)
- Tree Visualizer: Zoomable D3.js graph with branching, editing, influence mapping, and manual layout
- Collaboration: OAuth2 login, JWT-secured role-based access, GitHub issues import

Advanced & Integrations:
- Sub-prompt splitting, context injection (files, Jira/Notion), mind-map import/export, spec generation

Tech Stack:
- Frontend: React, TypeScript, Vite, D3.js, Shadcn UI
- Backend: Python 3.11, FastAPI, Uvicorn, Docker
- Database: MongoDB (+ optional PostgreSQL)
- Auth & AI: OAuth2/JWT, Google Gemini 2.5, OpenAI/GGML
- DevOps: Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD

